SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 974
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to congratulate the Walters State Community
College men's basketball team on winning the
TCCAA/Region 7 Championship.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly should pay tribute to those exemplary
student athletes who have attained the pinnacle of competition, thus bringing honor and acclaim
to the State of Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, the Walters State Community College men's basketball team epitomizes
excellence both on and off the basketball court; and
WHEREAS, the Walters State Senators recently enjoyed remarkable success with a 68-
65 victory over Columbia State to win the Tennessee Community College Athletic Association
(TCCAA)/Region 7 Championship; and
WHEREAS, the eighth such title in program history, the Walter State Senators improved
to a record of 30-1 on the season and advanced to the NJCAA DI basketball tournament for the
tenth time in school history; and
WHEREAS, the Senators were led by Taquez Butler, the TCCAA/Region 7 tournament
MVP, who tallied 15 points and 8 rebounds in the championship game; he finished the
tournament with a total of 49 points, 12 three-pointers, and 16 rebounds; and
WHEREAS, Walters State also received standout performances from Malaki Brooks and
Da'Mori Lytch who each scored 11 points, Tyrese Stovall with 10 points and seven rebounds,
Jamar Livingston with six points and three rebounds, Trae Rideau with five points, Jayden
Nesbitt with four points, Brian Carter with two points, four rebounds, and five assists, and
Jaquavious Wallace and Carter Webb with two points; and
SJR0974
015897
- 1 -

WHEREAS, through hard work and dedication, the members of the Walters State
Senators prepared themselves for all the challenges of this season, growing and improving both
as individual players and as a team; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Walters State Community College men's basketball
team have proven themselves to be deserving victors, and it is fitting that the team be honored;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the Walters State
Community College men's basketball team on winning the TCCAA/Region 7 Championship and
extend to them our best wishes for every continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
